     (Corrects author name in headline)  Joyce M. Roche, Avon's the first 
African American female vice president, former chief operating 
officer of Carson Products Company, and former Chief executive 
officer of the national nonprofit Girls Inc., and currently a 
board member at five Fortune 500 companies, discusses her book, 
"The Empress Has No Clothes: Conquering Self-Doubt to Embrace 
Success." She discusses "climbing the corporate ladder" and 
continually doubting her success, a prime example of "the 
imposter syndrome" which women, and men, often experience. Royce
spoke with Bloomberg's  Kathleen Hays  and Vonnie Quinn on Nov. 21
on  Bloomberg Radio 's "The Hays Advantage" at Bloomberg's Look 
Ahead to 2014 conference in Chicago.  (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 10:39
 